
// This Hyperlambda code snippet changes the value of the node referenced by the expression [@.name] to the value retrieved from the [name] node, which is a child of the [content] node, itself a child of the [http.post] node. The [set-value] slot is used to assign the retrieved value, while [get-value] is used to fetch the current value from the specified node path.
set-value:x:@.name
   get-value:x:@http.post/*/content/*/name
